Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @zucchini{1%unit} lengthwise; cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick
half-moons. Trim, peel, and cut @carrot{3%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick
pieces. Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1%unit} into ½-inch-thick wedges; mince
a few wedges until you have 2 TBSP. Dice @tomato{1%unit} into ½-inch pieces.

Toss zucchini, carrot, and onion wedges on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of
@cooking oil{2%teaspoon} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top
rack, tossing halfway through, until lightly browned and tender,
~{20-25%minutes}.

While veggies roast, in a #medium bowl{}, combine @ground pork{10%ounce}, minced
onion, half the @Tunisian spice blend{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest later),
and a pinch of salt and pepper. Form pork mixture into six 1 1/2-inch meatballs
(twelve meatballs for 4 servings).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large, preferably nonstick, pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add meatballs and press down with a #spatula{} to form patties; cook
until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

Transfer patties to a #plate{}; remove pan from heat and let cool slightly,
about ~{1%minute}.

> Ground Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

Heat same pan over medium heat. Add tomato and remaining Tunisian Spice Blend;
cook, stirring occasionally, until tomato is saucy, ~{3-4%minutes}.

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit}, half
the @flour{1%tablespoon} (all for 4 servings), and 1/3 cup water
(2/3 cup for 4). Slowly stir flour mixture into pan and cook, stirring
constantly, until sauce has thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove from heat; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted and
combined.

Divide vegetable jumble and pork patties between plates in separate sections.
Top patties with pan sauce and serve.